1.   An open area or square in a town where a public market or sale is set up. 2.   The world of business and commerce. 3.   A situation or place in which values, opinions, and ideas are put forward for debate or recognition:  a marketplace for new ideas; the literary marketplace. 1.   (Human Geography) a place where a public market is held 2.  any centre where ideas, opinions, etc, are exchanged 3.   (Commerce) the commercial world of buying and selling    1.   an open area in a town where a market is held.     2.   the world of business, trade, and economics. 